Valencia defender Ezequiel Garay, has confirmed that he has contracted Coronavirus. The 33-year-old also noted that 2020 has not gone to plan so far for him. The Argentine, who has been ruled out for the season with a cruciate ligament tear, made this known in a post on his official Instagram page on Sunday. Garay wrote: “It is clear that 2020 has got off on the wrong foot. “I have tested positive for the Coronavirus; I feel excellent, and now I have to listen to the health authorities. “For the time being, I am isolated.” Coronavirus, also known as COVID-19, has become a global problem with Europe now at the centre of the outbreak. Major sporting activities has now been put on hold in a bid to prevent the spread of the dreaded disease. The World Health Organisation (WHO) has since declared Coronavirus a global pandemic.